channel.title: Help? Can somone explain it to me?
channel.description:
I was reading this, trying to mess around on TestScape. I downloaded TestScape and all that, but half of this tutorial is poorly writted.
[url=http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,37596.0.html]http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,37596.0.html[/url]
Where do I find my IP and port number? :confused: Where do I type in my IP/port number? :confused: How do I find my server source? :confused: WTF? :confused: This tutorial is utterly and COMPLETLEY hard to understand. So will anyone please explain to me how to make a server quickly, effectively, and using words I can understand? Help is appreciated.

item.dc:creator: @IcyPimp IcyPimp
item.description:
@IcyPimp wrote:

Newb 2341:

Where do I find my IP and port number?

Go to Start(The little button in the bottom left of your computer) - All Programs - Acceccories - Command Prompt. Enter ipconfig. You should see your I.P. For the port, you’re just supposed to use 43594 or whatever.

Newb 2341:

How do I find my server source?

You should have downloaded one. Common sources are CheezScape, TestScape, Project16, etc. If you downloaded a different source, stop. Remove it, and download one of the ones listed. Nobody else knows how to code nowadays.
